You are given an array of integers. Your task is to calculate and print the factorial of each element in the array.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, representing the size of the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers, representing the array elements.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print the factorial of each array element separated by space.

Sample Input 0

5
0 1 2 3 4
Sample Output 0

1 1 2 6 24
Explanation 0

Factorial of 0 = 1

Factorial of 1 = 1

Factorial of 2 = 2

Factorial of 3 = 6

Factorial of 4 = 24



import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int a[]=new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) 
        {
            a[i]=sc.nextInt();
        }  
        int f=1;
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
                if(a[i]==0)
                a[i]=1;
                f*=a[i];
            System.out.print(f+" ");
            }
            }
        }
